<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-01-26-conjunction.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Arthur_Stanley_Eddington.jpg" width="250" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72638" /></p>
<blockquote><p>
We often think that when we have completed our study of <em>one</em> we know all about <em>two</em>, because &#8216;two&#8217; is &#8216;one and one&#8217;. We forget that we have still to make a study of &#8216;and&#8217;.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&#8212; Arthur Eddington, <a href="https://allais.wiki/priorartdocs/eddington.htm"><em>The Nature of the Physical World</em></a>, 1928</p>
